==English==
===Etymology===
From {{L.}} ''[[sextans]]'', a bronze coin worth one-sixth of an ''[[as#Latin|as]]''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sextant|sextants}}

[[Image:Sextant.gif|right|thumb|A nautical sextant]]
#{{nautical}}: A [[navigation]]al device for deriving [[angular distance]]s between objects so as to determine [[latitude]] and [[longitude]].
#{{mathematics}}: One [[sixth]] of a [[circle]] or [[disc]]; a [[sector]] with an [[angle]] of 60&deg;. 

